                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint's Copilot Integration Is Getting a Wider Rollout]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-word-excel-and-powerpoints-copilot-integration-is-getting-a-wider-rollout/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/office.jpg" length="135" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft 365 Personal]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Oh boy, more Copilot!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Microsoft has rolled out Copilot Chat and its suite of AI agents to a wider audience, bringing the unified AI chat directly into Microsoft 365 apps. This is a big deal because the full-featured Copilot chat panel was only for those with a paid plan.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 20:11:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-word-excel-and-powerpoints-copilot-integration-is-getting-a-wider-rollout/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Power Supply Is a Ticking Time Bomb—Know the Warning Signs]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-power-supply-is-a-ticking-time-bombknow-the-warning-signs/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2034838052.jpg" length="596" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[pc building]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hardware]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Pop goes the PC!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Power Supply Unit (PSU) in your desktop computer is the beating heart of the system.Without power your computer is a paperweight, but just like a sudden heart attack can ruin your day, a worn-out or faulty PSU can scrap your whole computer permanently.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-power-supply-is-a-ticking-time-bombknow-the-warning-signs/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[14 Hidden iOS 26 Features You Probably Missed]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hidden-ios-26-features-you-probably-missed/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/ios-26-dynamic-clock-on-lock-screen.png" length="3119" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[ios]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Intelligence]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Music]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Even Apple forgot to mention some of these.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>iOS 26 is here, and with it comes a new Liquid Glass design, interface overhauls for apps like Safari and Music, and support for the new iPhone 17 family of devices.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 19:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hidden-ios-26-features-you-probably-missed/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Reasons I Make Hard Copies of My Passwords]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-i-make-hard-copies-of-my-passwords/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_296332688.jpg" length="446" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[passwords]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cybersecurity]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cloud & Internet]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Giving digital a hard pass.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Common wisdom says that you should never write down your passwords, and for the most part I agree. Especially if you write it down on a sticky note attached to your screen bezel.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 19:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-i-make-hard-copies-of-my-passwords/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Buy vs. Lease a Car: Pros and Cons Explained]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/should-you-buy-or-lease-a-car/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tyler Dupont]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/model-s_70.jpg" length="238" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sedans]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Luxury Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><category><![CDATA[buying guide]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            We compare buying and leasing a car, outlining the advantages and drawbacks of each to help you choose wisely.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Deciding between buying and leasing a car is one of the most important choices for any driver, yet it’s not always straightforward. Both options come with distinct advantages and drawbacks, and understanding them can save you money while ensuring your vehicle meets your lifestyle needs.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/should-you-buy-or-lease-a-car/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Essential Skills Every PC User Should Have]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/essential-skills-every-pc-user-should-have/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/vintage-desktop-pc-with-floppy-drive-keyboard-and-mouse-in-neon-lightning.jpg" length="371" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The fist steps to PC independence.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>So you want to be a PC user that doesn't have to rely on IT support for every little thing? You want to deal with most issues on your own, and feel in control of your computer?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:15:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/essential-skills-every-pc-user-should-have/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[watchOS 26 Is Now Coming To An Apple Watch Near You]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/watchos-26-is-now-coming-to-an-apple-watch-near-you/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/apple-wwdc25-watchos-26-hero-250609.jpg" length="356" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[watchOS]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Less glass than on your iPhone, that's for certain.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>iOS 26, macOS 26, and iPadOS 26 are all here. But watchOS 26 is perhaps one of the most overlooked. Apple has just released its latest watch update, and like its cousins in other hardware, it’s very packed.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:10:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/watchos-26-is-now-coming-to-an-apple-watch-near-you/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[iOS 26 Is Finally Out With a Ton Of New Features]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ios-26-is-finally-out-with-a-ton-of-new-features/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/apple-wwdc25-ios-26-hero-250609.jpg" length="467" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[ios]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's glassy, but that's not the only thing it has going for it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>It’s been a long time coming. iOS 26 has been in the works for a long time, and it’s one of the wildest iOS updates we’ve seen in a long time. Now, it’s finally here—and it’s packing a heck of a lot of changes.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 18:06:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ios-26-is-finally-out-with-a-ton-of-new-features/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Pixel's Scam Detection Is About to Get Even Better]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pixels-scam-detection-is-about-to-get-even-better/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/a-phone-call-with-google-scam-call-detection.jpg" length="837" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Stopping junk in its tracks across all your apps. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you wish your Google Pixel's scam detection feature worked in more places, like your favorite chat apps or Instagram Messenger? If so, we have some potentially good news. This week, we learned that Google is getting ready to expand this great feature beyond calls and texts, making its phones safer than ever.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:54:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pixels-scam-detection-is-about-to-get-even-better/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[New York Wants to Restrict TikTok, YouTube, and Instagram]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-york-wants-to-restrict-tiktok-youtube-and-instagram/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/tiktok-logo-on-black-screen.jpg" length="129" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Social Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[instagram]]></category><category><![CDATA[YouTube]]></category><category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category><category><![CDATA[TikTok]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The latest age verification law to be proposed in the United States.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>New York is moving forward with a law that could force major social media platforms like TikTok, YouTube, and Instagram to roll out some form of age verification before minors can access their highly personalized, algorithm-driven feeds.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 17:47:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-york-wants-to-restrict-tiktok-youtube-and-instagram/</guid></item></channel>
